        <mxCell id="NBWsIPYUHiL5A0sF8qsy-67" parent="1" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="Header,Footer,&lt;div&gt;LogoName,Logo,&lt;br&gt;CompanyName,&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;EmailFooter,&lt;br&gt;DocumentationFooter,&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Home Page Notices&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="100" width="200" x="1340" y="630" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="NBWsIPYUHiL5A0sF8qsy-73" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="Async way of uploading assets to any bucket&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;(create workRequest to upload , but let&#39;s say there is problem with object storage , or internet is slow, worker requests will keep running, so we worker function , which terminates requests that run for more than 5 mins.&lt;br&gt;Trigger for worker function is canary" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="140" width="210" x="1310" y="800" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="NBWsIPYUHiL5A0sF8qsy-76" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: center; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(236, 236, 236); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; float: none; display: inline !important;&quot;&gt;What happens when copy operation fails during publish?&lt;br&gt;Copy file &amp;amp; publish operation is modelled as single transaction&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: center; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(236, 236, 236); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; float: none; display: inline !important;&quot;&gt;1.Copy all the assets&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: center; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(236, 236, 236); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; float: none; display: inline !important;&quot;&gt;2.Updating the manifest file&lt;br&gt;Partial copy files will not be used manifest is updated, Retry on&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: center; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(236, 236, 236); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; float: none; display: inline !important;&quot;&gt;failed pushed will overwrite any existing fiels&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="90" width="380" x="20" y="-330" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="NBWsIPYUHiL5A0sF8qsy-77" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="How does service manage loss of data during upload/move operations?&lt;div&gt;Case1 Client can upload the file again if upload is failed&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Case2: From copying one bucket to other, as it is a copy operation not move&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;so data will remain intact in source bucket&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="530" x="460" y="-340" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="NBWsIPYUHiL5A0sF8qsy-78" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="How to achieve mutually exclusive write operation in object storage?&lt;div&gt;When two or more clients tries to update metadat.json file at a same time, once can overwrite changes done by other, it can lead to inconsistent state, we would rely on Optimistic Concurrency Control Strategy offered by Object Storage Every Object has an Etag associated with them&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;GetObject , update the object, PutObject only if match etag with getObject&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;operation&lt;br&gt;Operation fails with Etag mismatch then it return 409 conflict state&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="120" width="440" x="50" y="-220" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="NBWsIPYUHiL5A0sF8qsy-80" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="How to copy artificats from one bucket to another?&lt;br&gt;We use CopyObjectAPI, it is async API &amp;amp; it returns workRequest id, which UXConfig Service use to poll therequest status" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="90" width="352" x="605" y="-240" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="NBWsIPYUHiL5A0sF8qsy-81" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="How the content of UXConfig.json is updated?&lt;br&gt;We don&#39;t have html css there we have assets &amp;amp; every asset has accosiated themeOcid which we get from branding plugin,&lt;div&gt;so in object storage we have directory with that ocid &amp;amp; we go &amp;amp; change the assets there &amp;amp; frontend will get json file can fetch the data from the specified location&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="100" width="430" x="570" y="-130" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="EhV8c7pBepqpBrJFcm9V-1" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Connecting to object storage&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; totalOpenConnections(40)&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; ttlInSeconds(4)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;maxRetries(5)&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;initialRetryDelayMilliseconds(100)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;maxRetryDelayMilliseconds(1000)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;defaultMaxConnectionsPerRoute(10);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="120" width="230" x="610" y="880" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
